title: Frieze, 1905–15
inscribed: Printed in selvedge: "Hobbs. Benton & Heath."; pattern number "3380" "FM"
description: Mission/art nouveau style. Large floral pendants and swags of pink roses and green leaves, outlined by a tin cream-colored leafy vine, which hang from a brown knotted ribbon outlined by beading and the same leafy vine. Ground shades dark to light beige from bottom to top. Printed in selvedge: "Hobbs. Benton & Heath."; pattern number "3380" "FM"

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1905–15.
1905–15. Machine-printed on paper. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-387.
